  {
    "additions": 9,
    "author": {
      "id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQ1MjQzMjM2",
      "is_bot": false,
      "login": "haakon-e",
      "name": "Haakon Ludvig Langeland Ervik"
    },
    "body": "Finally fixes NaN-inconsistencies that has plagued us for a while.\r\n\r\nSince we don't run 1-moment microphysics, the \"abstract\" version of `compute_precipitation_sink_tendencies` is used to compute precipitation sink tendencies. The 1M version computed tendencies for precipitation sinks of `qt` and `e_tot`, which is used in `compute_gm_tendencies!` to compute grid-mean tendencies for `\u03c1q_tot` and `\u03c1e_tot`. \r\n\r\nIn the non-1M-case, these precipitation sink tendencies are not set at all.\r\n\r\nThis PR sets these tendencies to zero.\r\n\r\nRef: #1039, #1037.\r\n\r\nCloses: #1017",
    "changedFiles": 1,
